sentiment_score_definition: x <= -0.35: Bearish; -0.35 < x <= -0.15: Somewhat-Bearish; -0.15 < x < 0.15: Neutral; 0.15 <= x < 0.35: Somewhat_Bullish; x >= 0.35: Bullish
relevance_score_definition: 0 < x <= 1, with a higher score indicating higher relevance.

feed.title: Barclays Lifts Omnicom (OMC) Target to $90 Following In-Line Q4 Results
feed.summary: Barclays has increased its price target for Omnicom Group Inc. (OMC) to $90 from $82, maintaining an Equal Weight rating, after the company's Q4 results met expectations. Omnicom's Chairman and CEO, John Wren, announced plans to divest non-core businesses generating $2.5 billion in revenue and revealed a doubling of expected annual run-rate synergies to $1.5 billion, with $900 million anticipated in 2026. The company also authorized a $5 billion share repurchase program, already initiating a $2.5 billion accelerated buyback.

feed.title: Here's What Analysts Are Saying About Expedia Group (EXPE)
feed.summary: Analysts have mixed views on Expedia Group (EXPE) following its Q4 results and 2026 guide. DA Davidson and Susquehanna both cut price targets while maintaining Neutral ratings, citing concerns about EBITDA margin expansion and balanced risk/reward. BMO Capital, however, raised its price target while maintaining a Market Perform rating.

feed.title: RBC Capital Initiates Blackstone (BX) Coverage with $179 Target on Strong Growth Outlook
feed.summary: RBC Capital has initiated coverage on Blackstone Inc. (BX) with an Outperform rating and a $179 price target, citing the firm's "first-mover advantage" in private wealth and its strong position to benefit from long-term retail investor growth and an improving real estate cycle. The analyst also highlighted Blackstone's recent acquisition of Champions Group, a home services provider, through its BXPE strategy, further bolstering its diverse investment portfolio.

feed.title: Is It Too Late To Consider McKesson (MCK) After Its Powerful Multi‑Year Rally?
feed.summary: McKesson (MCK) has seen significant share price appreciation over the past several years, with returns of 57.6% over the last year. Despite this strong rally, Simply Wall St's Discounted Cash Flow (DCF) analysis suggests the stock is currently undervalued by 34.2%. Its P/E ratio of 27.50x is comparable to industry averages, and a proprietary "Fair Ratio" also indicates undervaluation.

feed.title: Mosaic Resets Operations With Cost Cuts Record Output And Biosciences Growth
feed.summary: Mosaic (NYSE:MOS) is implementing a comprehensive operational reset focusing on cost savings, achieving record production in phosphate and potash, and divesting noncore assets after a challenging fourth quarter. The company is also expanding its higher-margin Biosciences division with new product launches and doubling annual sales. These strategic shifts aim to enhance efficiency, simplify the portfolio, and position Mosaic for more consistent profitability, with particular attention to capital discipline and working capital release.

feed.title: Sysco (SYY) Declares Consistent Quarterly Dividend
feed.summary: Sysco Corporation (SYY) has announced it will maintain its quarterly dividend at $0.54 per share, resulting in a 2.42% forward yield. The company aims for at least 2.5% local case growth in the latter half of 2026, supported by strong financial health and market position. Sysco faces risks from high leverage and debt issuance but shows strong financial health indicators.

feed.title: Truist Lifts Centene (CNC) Target to $49, Maintains Buy Rating After Positive Management Meetings
feed.summary: Truist has raised its price target for Centene Corporation (CNC) to $49 from $47, while maintaining a Buy rating. The firm's bullish stance follows positive meetings with Centene's management, citing meaningful margin opportunities and steady improvement from current initiatives. Centene's CEO reported an adjusted diluted loss per share of ($1.19) for Q4 2025 but expects full-year 2026 adjusted EPS to exceed $3, representing over 40% year-over-year growth.

feed.title: Barclays Lowers Humana (HUM) Price Target amid Questions on Margin Expansion Outlook
feed.summary: Barclays has lowered its price target for Humana (HUM) to $176 from $245, maintaining an Equal Weight rating, due to increased caution regarding the company's outlook for doubling Individual Medicare Advantage margins. This comes as Humana recently acquired Florida-based MaxHealth for an estimated $1 billion, expanding its primary care network amidst pressures on its Medicare Advantage business from rising costs and stricter government reimbursement. The acquisition aims to support Humana's broader strategy to enhance primary care services through its CenterWell Senior Primary Care division.

feed.title: SkyWater Technology (SKYT) Q4 Loss Challenges Bullish Narrative After Q3 EPS Surge
feed.summary: SkyWater Technology (SKYT) reported mixed results for FY 2025, with a significant Q3 EPS jump to US$2.98 followed by a Q4 loss of US$0.16. Despite a full year of positive trailing earnings (US$2.47 EPS), three out of four quarters in FY 2025 were loss-making, raising questions about margin quality and the sustainability of profits. The company's low P/E ratio compared to peers conflicts with a DCF fair value significantly below its current share price, while concerns about debt coverage and projected earnings declines present a challenge for the bullish outlook.

feed.title: Sun Life posts $1.1b as competitors trail by $200m
feed.summary: Sun Life of Canada (Philippines), Inc. reported a total premium income of $1.1 billion (PHP61.8 billion) for FY 2025, maintaining its market leadership in the Philippines for the 15th consecutive year. The company surpassed its nearest competitor by $0.2 billion (PHP8.9 billion). Sun Life plans to enhance its digital capabilities and expand its advisor network in the current year.

feed.title: Is IQVIA Holdings Inc. (IQV) a Buy Post Earnings?
feed.summary: Mizuho, Truist, and TD Cowen have adjusted their price targets for IQVIA Holdings Inc. (IQV) following its fiscal Q4 report and re-segmentation, with ratings ranging from Outperform to Hold. Analysts are considering the potential impact of AI disruption on the company, which provides advanced analytics, clinical research, and technology solutions for the life sciences industry. While IQV is seen as a strong buy by some, the article suggests that certain AI stocks may offer greater upside potential with less downside risk.

feed.title: Here's What Analysts Think About Thermo Fisher Scientific (TMO) Post Earnings
feed.summary: Thermo Fisher Scientific Inc. (TMO) reported strong Q4 and full-year 2025 results, with significant revenue and EPS growth. Following these positive earnings, analysts from Citi and Baird raised their price targets for the stock and maintained Buy/Outperform ratings, highlighting its continued potential as a top healthcare investment. The company specializes in analytical instruments and services for various scientific fields.

feed.title: Coterra Energy Reports 2025 Results, Provides 2026 Guidance, and Announces Quarterly Dividend
feed.summary: Coterra Energy Inc. reported strong fourth-quarter and full-year 2025 results, exceeding production guidance and generating significant cash flow. The company also provided 2026 guidance, emphasizing capital efficiency, and announced a quarterly dividend of $0.22 per share. Additionally, Coterra highlighted its planned all-stock merger with Devon Energy, expected to close in the second quarter of 2026, which aims to create an industry-leading shale operator with enhanced free cash flow and shareholder returns.

feed.title: Wedbush Cautious on Best Buy (BBY) Ahead of Q4 Earnings
feed.summary: Wedbush has reduced its target price for Best Buy (BBY) to $70 from $80, maintaining a Neutral rating ahead of the company's Q4 FY 2026 earnings report. The firm cited low investor expectations due to weak holiday sales and ongoing memory supply shortages. Wedbush also expressed concern over potential disappointing forward guidance for FY 2027, anticipating a decline in same-store sales.

feed.title: Why Take-Two Interactive Software (TTWO) Is Up 5.9% After Earnings Beat And GTA VI Buzz – And What's Next
feed.summary: Take-Two Interactive Software (TTWO) saw its stock rise 5.9% after reporting earnings and revenue that exceeded analyst expectations, leading to upward revisions in forecasts. The company's investment narrative is heavily tied to the anticipated release of Grand Theft Auto VI in November 2026 and its ability to deliver on future AAA titles. Despite current losses and high investment, analysts project significant revenue and earnings growth by 2028, leading to a fair value estimate that suggests a 30% upside.

feed.title: What Does the Street Think About Boston Scientific Corporation (BSX)?
feed.summary: Boston Scientific Corporation (BSX) has been highlighted as a strong buy healthcare stock, with recent board appointments and earnings reports attracting attention. The company announced robust net sales growth for both fiscal Q4 and the full year 2025, leading to reaffirmations of Buy ratings from some analysts, although one firm slightly reduced its price target. Boston Scientific is known for developing and marketing medical devices across cardiovascular and MedSurg segments.

feed.title: Former Georgia Home Depot employee sentenced in $4 million gift card scheme
feed.summary: A former Home Depot employee, Felecia Ingram, has been sentenced to over three years in federal prison and ordered to pay nearly $3.95 million in restitution for a $4 million gift card scheme. Ingram stole over 8,000 physical gift cards, activated them using false orders, and then deleted the orders to conceal the theft. She sold the cards on the black market to fund an "extravagant gambling lifestyle."

feed.title: Where is Danaher Corporation (DHR) Headed?
feed.summary: Danaher Corporation (DHR) recently declared a quarterly cash dividend of $0.40 per share and announced a definitive agreement to acquire Masimo Corporation for approximately $9.9 billion. This acquisition is expected to accelerate Danaher's Diagnostics segment's core revenue growth. The article suggests that while DHR is a strong investment, certain AI stocks might offer greater upside potential.

feed.title: Truist Raised Target Price on Sonoco Products (SON) to $69, Following Investor Day
feed.summary: Truist analyst Michael Roxland raised his target price on Sonoco Products (SON) to $69 and reiterated a Buy recommendation following the company's Investor Day. Sonoco Products presented achievable near- and medium-term guidance, targeting a 200-basis-point expansion in adjusted EBITDA margins to reach $1.5 billion by 2028, and $2.5 billion in cumulative cash flow from operations over three years. The company, a manufacturer of industrial and consumer packaging, also aims for a long-term net leverage below 2.5x by 2028, with its CEO noting a streamlined focus for consistent earnings growth and efficient capital allocation.

feed.title: Stephens Raised Target Price on SM Energy (SM) to $49, Following Divesture of Some South Texas Assets
feed.summary: Stephens has increased its target price for SM Energy (SM) to $49, up from $48, while maintaining an "Overweight" rating. This adjustment follows SM Energy's recent announcement of selling some South Texas assets to Caturus Energy for $950 million. The divested assets, comprising 61,000 net acres with 260 wells and 168 MMboe in reserves, are expected to generate 37-39 Mboe/d and $160 million in annual cash flows, with the proceeds slated for debt reduction.

feed.title: 2026 NTT INDYCAR SERIES Season on SiriusXM
feed.summary: SiriusXM announced comprehensive coverage of the 2026 NTT INDYCAR SERIES season, beginning March 1st with the Firestone Grand Prix of St. Petersburg. Subscribers will have live access to all 18 events, including the Indianapolis 500, plus qualifying and practice sessions on the SiriusXM INDYCAR Nation channel. The coverage also includes new seasons of "Brick-by-Brick," the "Off Track with Hinch & Rossi" podcast, and a continued sponsorship collaboration with Meyer Shank Racing featuring special car liveries.

feed.title: Rhythm Pharmaceuticals Files For Mixed Shelf
feed.summary: Rhythm Pharmaceuticals (RYTM) has filed for a mixed shelf offering, according to a report by Refinitiv. This type of filing allows a company to issue various types of securities, such as common stock, preferred stock, debt securities, or warrants, over a period of time. The article is very brief and does not provide further details on the specific terms or timing of the offering.

feed.title: Citi Raised Target Price on Omnicom (OMC) to $115
feed.summary: Citi analyst Jason Bazinet increased the target price for Omnicom (OMC) to $115 from $103, maintaining a Buy recommendation after the company's strong Q4 2025 results. Omnicom reported a 25% YoY growth in adjusted operating income, doubled its cost synergy forecast from the Interpublic acquisition to $1.5 billion, and approved a new $5 billion share repurchase program. The company plans to execute $500 million to $1 billion in buybacks during 2026.

feed.title: Cottage Cheese Recall Hits Walmart Stores in 24 States
feed.summary: Walmart has issued a recall for its Great Value brand cottage cheese across 24 states because the liquid dairy ingredients used were not properly pasteurized. This oversight raises concerns about potential contamination from bacteria like Salmonella and E. coli, which pasteurization is designed to eliminate. Consumers are advised to dispose of the affected products or return them to Walmart for a full refund.

feed.title: Invitation Homes to Participate in Citi's 2026 Global Property CEO Conference
feed.summary: Invitation Homes Inc. announced its management team will attend Citi's 2026 Global Property CEO Conference on Monday, March 2, 2026, for a roundtable discussion. A live audio webcast of the presentation will be available on the company's Investor Relations website, with a replay accessible through April 2, 2026. Invitation Homes is a leading single-family home leasing and management company.

feed.title: Is CME Group (CME) Pricing Leave Room After Strong Multi‑Year Share Gains
feed.summary: CME Group (CME) has seen significant share gains over multiple years, prompting an analysis of whether its current US$302.48 share price is overvalued. Using an Excess Returns analysis and a Price-to-Earnings comparison, the article suggests that CME Group may be overvalued by approximately 29.8% and is trading above its modeled "Fair Ratio" P/E of 15.80x. Investors are encouraged to use Simply Wall St's "Narratives" feature for a more personalized valuation model.

feed.title: Citi Raised Target Price on Omnicom (OMC) to $115
feed.summary: Citi analyst Jason Bazinet has raised his target price for Omnicom (OMC) to $115 from $103, maintaining a Buy recommendation. This increase follows Omnicom's strong Q4 2025 results, which reported a 25% year-over-year growth in adjusted operating income. The company also doubled its forecast for annual cost synergies from the Interpublic acquisition to $1.5 billion and approved a $5 billion share repurchase program.

feed.title: Sunstone Hotel Investors faces earnings test amid peer concerns By Investing.com
feed.summary: Sunstone Hotel Investors is set to report its fourth-quarter results, with analysts anticipating a sequential improvement in EPS despite continuing industry headwinds. The company faces scrutiny on its operational efficiency and portfolio positioning, especially after a recent downgrade, as investors look for signs of margin defense and recovery in a challenging market. The upcoming report will be critical in demonstrating Sunstone's ability to compete in a bifurcated lodging sector.

feed.title: Broadridge Study: Financial Institutions Shift GenAI From Pilot Programs to Scaled Deployment
feed.summary: A new study by Broadridge Financial Solutions reveals that financial institutions are rapidly moving from piloting generative AI to scaled deployment, with 80% now using GenAI or predictive AI in operations, a significant jump from 31% last year. The report highlights a decline in ROI concerns and an increase in firms reporting measurable business benefits from GenAI initiatives, including growing adoption and reported returns in the Asia Pacific region. This shift indicates that AI is proving its capability to modernize the financial industry at speed.

feed.title: Goldman Sachs Raises its Price Target on A. O. Smith Corporation (AOS) to $69 from $63
feed.summary: Goldman Sachs has raised its price target on A. O. Smith Corporation (AOS) to $69 from $63, while maintaining a Sell rating. The firm anticipates a deceleration in housing and industry dynamics, limiting upside for 2026 due to macro headwinds and tough comparisons in China, though it sees potential for higher earnings long-term through expanded offerings and secular growth. This comes after other analysts like Stifel and Baird also adjusted their price targets following A.O. Smith's mixed Q4 results, where adjusted EPS beat consensus but revenue guidance was light.

feed.title: Truist Raises its Price Target on Vulcan Materials Company (VMC) to $360 and Maintains a Buy Rating
feed.summary: Truist has raised its price target for Vulcan Materials Company (VMC) to $360 from $320, maintaining a Buy rating despite a Q4 earnings miss. The firm noted that the 2026 outlook still indicates year-over-year growth, with modest volume growth guidance unchanged. RBC Capital also adjusted its price target to $296 from $316, keeping a Sector Perform rating, suggesting that Vulcan may provide more updates at its upcoming Capital Markets Day.

feed.title: Scotiabank Raises its Price Target on FirstEnergy Corp. (FE) to $56 and Maintains an Outperform Rating
feed.summary: Scotiabank has increased its price target for FirstEnergy Corp. (FE) to $56 from $55 while maintaining an Outperform rating. This upgrade follows FirstEnergy's announcement of a $36 billion capital investment plan for 2026-2030, representing a significant 30% increase over the previous plan and aiming for 10% compounded annual rate base growth. The company expects this plan to drive core EPS compounded annual growth near the top end of its 6%-8% target range.

feed.title: Want Sachem Capital’s 2025 numbers? Earnings webcast set for March 13
feed.summary: Sachem Capital (SACH) announced it will release its fourth-quarter and full-year 2025 financial results after market close on Thursday, March 12, 2026. A webcast and conference call to discuss these results will be held on Friday, March 13, 2026, at 8:00 a.m. ET. Investors can access the live webcast via the company's website or participate by telephone.

feed.title: Hormel Foods (HRL) Margin Compression Tests Bullish Earnings Growth Narrative In Q1 2026
feed.summary: Hormel Foods (HRL) reported Q1 2026 revenue of approximately US$3.0 billion and basic EPS of US$0.33, indicating steady revenues but challenging profitability. The company faces margin compression with a trailing net profit margin of 4% (down from 6.4% a year ago), even as earnings are forecasted to grow faster than revenue. Investors are presented with conflicting signals, including a rich P/E ratio, an unsustainably covered dividend, and a significant discounted cash flow (DCF) upside, making the durability of Hormel's margin profile a key concern.

feed.title: Assessing Regeneron Pharmaceuticals (REGN) Valuation After Dupixent’s New FDA Approval For Allergic Fungal Rhinosinusitis
feed.summary: Regeneron Pharmaceuticals (REGN) recently received FDA approval for Dupixent to treat allergic fungal rhinosinusitis, expanding its labeled uses. Despite this positive news and other pipeline developments, the company's stock momentum has been modest. Simply Wall St assesses REGN as undervalued at $770.79, with a narrative fair value of $821.12, attributing the gap to expectations for revenue growth from EYLEA HD, firm profit margins, and anticipated future earnings multiples, though risks like competition and pipeline disappointments remain.

feed.title: RBC Capital Raises its Price Target on Global Payments Inc. (GPN) to $97 and Maintains a Sector Perform Rating
feed.summary: RBC Capital has increased its price target for Global Payments Inc. (GPN) to $97 from $95, maintaining a Sector Perform rating after the company's strong Q4 earnings and "appropriately level-set" FY26 guidance. Other analysts, including TD Cowen and UBS, also raised their price targets on GPN following its Q4 performance and 2026 outlook. Global Payments reported Q4 adjusted EPS of $3.18 and adjusted revenue of $2.32 billion, aligning with consensus, and highlighted 2025 as a "transformative year" with progress in its operating platform.

feed.title: Iowa attorney general suing General Motors over data privacy concerns
feed.summary: Iowa Attorney General Brenna Bird is suing General Motors, alleging the company illegally collected and sold Iowans' driving data without their knowledge or consent since 2015. The lawsuit claims GM sold this data to third-party brokers, who then sold it to insurance companies, leading to increased rates or canceled policies for consumers. Bird seeks restitution for affected Iowans and an injunction to stop GM's data collection practices in the state.

feed.title: Sonida Senior Living shareholders approve key proposals at special meeting By Investing.com
feed.summary: Sonida Senior Living (NYSE:SNDA) shareholders approved several key proposals at a special meeting, including an increase in authorized common stock and the issuance of shares related to its merger with CNL Healthcare Properties, Inc. They also approved amendments to the company's charter regarding stockholder nominations and indemnification of directors and officers. These measures are pivotal for facilitating the upcoming merger and updating corporate governance.

feed.title: Intuit Inc (NASDAQ:INTU) Shares Dip Despite Strong Q2 Earnings Beat
feed.summary: Intuit Inc. (NASDAQ:INTU) reported strong fiscal second-quarter earnings that surpassed analyst expectations, driven by robust growth in its Global Business Solutions and Consumer Group segments, particularly TurboTax and Credit Karma. Despite these positive results, the stock dipped in after-hours trading due to a cautious forward outlook and planned increases in marketing spending for the upcoming tax season. Investors are weighing the strong performance against potential short-term profit impacts from increased customer acquisition costs.

feed.title: Morgan Stanley Raises its Price Target on Edison International (EIX) to $68 from $61
feed.summary: Morgan Stanley raised its price target on Edison International (EIX) to $68 from $61, maintaining an Underweight rating, citing the utility sector's underperformance. This follows strong Q4 earnings where Edison International exceeded consensus estimates, reported a 2.3% residential rate decrease, and reaffirmed its long-term growth target. Another analyst, Shelby Tucker from TD Cowen, also increased their price target to $83 with a Buy rating.

feed.title: SoundThinking technology adoption expands across Louisiana law enforcement
feed.summary: Law enforcement agencies across Louisiana are increasingly adopting SoundThinking technology to enhance public safety and operational efficiency. This includes deploying real-time gunshot detection systems and integrating advanced case management tools, reflecting a broader trend of digital transformation in policing. The goal is to improve response times and support investigations, ultimately leading to faster and more effective protection for communities.

feed.title: SM Energy Q4 2025 Earnings Beat Estimates, Revenue Misses Forecasts - News and Statistics
feed.summary: SM Energy Co. reported its Q4 and full-year 2025 financial results. For Q4, the company's net income was $109 million, with adjusted earnings of 83 cents per share, surpassing analyst expectations of 73 cents per share. However, the reported revenue of $705 million fell short of the $765.6 million forecast by analysts.

feed.title: IonQ Crushes Q4 Estimates— Rigetti, Quantum Computing On Deck
feed.summary: IonQ (NYSE: IONQ) significantly exceeded its fourth-quarter revenue estimates, reporting $61.9 million, a 429% increase year-over-year, and became the first pure-play quantum firm to reach $100 million in annual revenue. This performance has boosted the entire quantum computing sector, demonstrating commercial viability and investor confidence. While D-Wave Quantum (NYSE: QBTS) reported a revenue miss, it showed strong bookings growth, and the quantum community now looks to upcoming reports from Rigetti Computing (NASDAQ: RGTI) and Quantum Computing (NASDAQ: QUBT) to gauge continued sector momentum.

feed.title: Pre-market top loser ZBH.SW Zimmer Biomet -4.26% on 27 Feb 2026: support CHF67.50
feed.summary: Zimmer Biomet (ZBH.SW) started trading on February 27, 2026, as the top pre-market loser on the SIX Swiss Exchange, declining -4.26% to CHF67.50. This drop is attributed to weak near-term momentum and a significant gap from its 50- and 200-day averages, alongside low liquidity amplifying the price movement. While Meyka AI gives ZBH.SW a B+ grade with a "BUY" suggestion, forecasts indicate potential further downside for the stock, urging traders to watch for the May 2026 earnings report and the CHF67.50 support level.

feed.title: Did Record Q1 Results and Buybacks Just Reframe Bank of Montreal's (TSX:BMO) Earnings Power?
feed.summary: Bank of Montreal (TSX:BMO) reported record Q1 2026 results with higher net interest income and net income, alongside a significant share buyback, indicating strong earnings power and balance sheet resilience. The bank's performance, particularly in U.S. and capital markets, reinforces its investment narrative of diversified growth and consistent capital returns, despite potential risks from rising technology and staffing costs. These results provide investors with fresh data to assess the bank's future earnings and fair value estimates.

feed.title: Assessing Regeneron Pharmaceuticals (REGN) Valuation After Dupixent’s New FDA Approval For Allergic Fungal Rhinosinusitis
feed.summary: Regeneron Pharmaceuticals recently received FDA approval for Dupixent for allergic fungal rhinosinusitis, expanding the drug's labeled uses. Despite this positive news and other pipeline advancements, REGN's share price momentum has been modest. The article suggests that REGN, currently trading at $770.79, appears to be undervalued compared to a narrative fair value of $821.12, driven by expected revenue growth, strong profit margins, and future earnings potential, though risks like competition for Eylea exist.

feed.title: Meta Platforms CFO Li sells $35.3 million in stock By Investing.com
feed.summary: Meta Platforms CFO Susan J. Li sold 58,478 shares of Class A Common Stock for approximately $35.3 million on February 24, 2026, through a trust. These transactions were executed under a pre-arranged trading plan. Despite the insider sale, Meta maintains strong financial health with high gross profit margins, and its stock is considered slightly undervalued according to InvestingPro analysis, while the company also faces legal actions against scam advertisers and has secured an agreement with AMD for AI infrastructure.

feed.title: Truist Raises the Price Target on Quanta Services, Inc. (PWR) to $643 and Maintains a Buy Rating
feed.summary: Truist has raised its price target on Quanta Services, Inc. (PWR) to $643 from $548, maintaining a Buy rating after the company's strong Q4 earnings, driven by Electric Infrastructure performance and acquisitions. Other analysts like DA Davidson and Cantor Fitzgerald also increased their price targets, citing solid results and a strong position in infrastructure with significant backlog. Quanta Services reported Q4 adjusted EPS of $3.16 and revenue of $7.84B, surpassing consensus expectations.

feed.title: Ryerson Reports Q4 Loss
feed.summary: Ryerson Holding Corp., a Chicago-based metals distributor, reported a $37.9 million loss in its fourth-quarter earnings report. This loss is attributed to lower sales volumes and pricing pressures, reflecting broader challenges in the industrial sector. The company's performance serves as an indicator for economic conditions in manufacturing, construction, and transportation industries.

feed.title: Emerson Electric Shares Surge 2.88% on Strong Earnings and Guidance Hike Despite $400M Volume Ranking 349th
feed.summary: Emerson Electric (EMR) shares rose by 2.88% after the company reported strong Q1 2026 earnings, surpassing EPS estimates and matching revenue projections. The company also raised its full-year guidance, forecasting increased EPS and annual sales growth, driven by strategic initiatives and alignment with secular tailwinds like electrification and energy security. Investor confidence was further boosted by a $250 million share repurchase program, a $10 billion shareholder return target by 2028, and upward adjustments to price targets by analysts.
